CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 24, 1946, pg. 9 reads: "National master - Mrs. Anne Sublette of Chicago won the national master's in National Bridge Tournament currently being held in Pittsburgh. The play-off, held Sunday, had Mrs. Sublette first and Alan Parkinson of New York, second. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Anne Sublette wearing ribbon inscribed "13th Annual Tournament American..."  playing bridge in Kay Boys Club during Thirteenth Annual Conference of the American Bridge Association
